title: SFF2023 - DIGITALISATION IN COFFEE ROASTING
description: In this workshop, we aim to showcase how the coffee industry has evolved through technology, and how it has revolutionized the roasting process. As coffee enthusiasts and professionals, we understand the importance of staying ahead in an ever-evolving digital landscape. From advanced data analytics to automated roasting profiles, we will delve into the cutting-edge techniques that are shaping the future of coffee roasting. Join us for an interactive session filled with insightful discussions, hands-on demonstrations, and a taste of the what it's like to be a coffee roaster. Get ready to embrace the digital revolution and unlock new possibilities in the art of smart roasting! #SkillsFutureSG #SkillsFutureFestival2023 Date: 16th July 2023 Time: 8:30AM to 10:30AM Location: Lifelong Learning Institute, Training Room 1-2. *Guests encouraged to arrive 10 mins before the session starts. *Price are subject to 8% GST. *Tickets sold are non-refundable and exchangeable.

title: CAFEC TH-2 SPECIALTY FILTER PAPER
description: Introducing the CAFEC TH-2 Specialty Filter Paper. title: ANIS UDAINI
description: ORIGIN Yemen ALTITUDE 1900 m.a.s.l PROCESS Natural PROFILE Floral, Mandarine, Nuts This Yemen coffee, grown at 1900 MASL in the Anis region, features the Udaini cultivar and undergoes the natural process, where the coffee cherries dry with the pulp intact. This method imparts rich, fruit-forward flavors, enhancing the coffee’s floral, mandarin, and nutty notes. The high altitude contributes to the beans' bright acidity and complex, well-structured body, resulting in a vibrant and nuanced cup. SEPTEMBER RELEASE | FILTER | 250G

title: NEPAL SINDHUPALCHOK
description: ORIGIN Nepal ALTITUDE 1000 - 2200 m.a.s.l PROCESS Washed / Natural PROFILE Raisin, Chestnut, Sugarcane Nepali coffee, primarily Arabica varieties like Bourbon and Typica, is organically grown at altitudes of 1000–1600 meters in over 40 districts. Known for its unique flavor, aroma, and body, it thrives beyond traditional coffee belts, offering high environmental and economic value. Handpicked coffee cherries are processed using wet or dry methods, showcasing Nepal's sustainable cultivation practices. FEBRUARY RELEASE | FILTER | 200G

title: CESAR BUESAQUILLO
description: ORIGIN Colombia, Esmeralda ALTITUDE 1750 - 18 00 m.a.s.l PROCESS Natural Anaerobic PROFILE Chardonnay, Red Grapes, Berries This micro-lot coffee, grown by Cesar Buesaquillo at La Esmeralda, is 100% Pink Bourbon. Hand-picked for ripeness, the cherries underwent 40 hours of anaerobic fermentation, then were sun-dried to optimal moisture. The Pink Bourbon varietal, believed to be a mutation from San Adolfo, Huila at 2100m, is still being studied for its origins. FEBRUARY RELEASE | FILTER | 200G

JULY RELEASE | FILTER | 150G

title: TOFFEE LUCK
description: ORIGIN El Savador, Metapán ALTITUDE 1720 m.a.s.l PROCESS Natural PROFILE Chocolate Milk, Hazelnut, Apricot Toffee Luck is a naturally processed Pacamara coffee from El Salvador’s award-winning Finca El Izotal, grown at 1,720 MASL.
